go here:

http://www.stack.nl/~dimitri/doxygen/download.html#latestsrc

get this for Mac OS X 10.5 (Leopard) and 10.6 (Snow Leopard):

http://ftp.stack.nl/pub/users/dimitri/Doxygen-1.7.1.dmg

copy to applications.

then do something like this to get the binaries in the path:

$ sudo cp /Applications/Doxygen.app/Contents/Resources/[a-z]* /usr/local/bin/.

---

right now javadoc and native are enabled. i personally use javadoc for
multiline but native //! for oneliners.
